Chris Obure was charged with assault on Thursday for allegedly attacking and threatening to shoot a reveller.The 36-year-old 'gold dealer' is said to have attacked Ben Alila at B-Longue in Kilimani, Nairobi, on New Year's Eve.He denied the charges before Milimani senior principal magistrate Joyce Gandani.Gandani granted Obure a bond of Sh50,000 or a cash bail of Sh20,000 and set a hearing for March 9.The prosecution has listed six witnesses including three police officers.More on this: 'Gold dealer' Chris Obure arrested for threatening to shoot reveller in club